title: Two Sum
description: Given an array of integers nums and an integer target, return indices of the two numbers such that they add up to target.
inputStatement: First line contains integer n. Second line contains n integers. Third line contains target integer.
outputStatement: Output two integers representing indices of the numbers.

title: Add Two Numbers
description: You are given two non-empty linked lists representing two non-negative integers.
inputStatement: First line contains n. Second line contains n digits of first number. Third line contains m. Fourth line contains m digits of second number.
outputStatement: Output digits of the sum in reverse order.
constraints: The number of nodes in each linked list is in the range [1, 100].
